// useDocumentHistory
// Fetches and exposes the version history for a single document.

History is re-fetched whenever documentId, project, or session changes.
A 404 response is treated as "no history yet" rather than an error.

FUNCTION useDocumentHistory(documentId) -> { history, isLoading, error, refetch, getVersionAt }  EXPORT
  CALLS: useSession (useSession)
  Manages state: history, isLoading, error.
  On mount (and when documentId changes), calls fetchHistory. Clears history if documentId is null.

---

FUNCTION fetchHistory()
  Fetches /api/document/{documentId}/history with project and session as query params.
  IF 404, sets history to null (not an error). IF ok, stores the parsed history. ELSE sets error.

---

FUNCTION getVersionAt(timestamp) -> string | null
  Fetches /api/document/{documentId}/version with project, session, and timestamp as query params.
  Returns the content string on success, or null on failure.
